bug.short_desc: Fedora Does Not Honor Selection Color Configuration
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I made all steps to configure appropriately Bluefish Configuration. Regarding Selection, Fedora shows, Anyway, Environment config.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Fedora 24 x86_64; BlueFish 2.2.9-1
How reproducible: Try to configure (Edit --> Preferences --> Editor Configuration, Font &Color
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Config; 2. Try to select something; 3. Bluefish shows selection with Environment data, even your configuration say contraryly.
Actual results: Bluefish shows everybody Environment colors
Expected results: Show color selected.
Additional info: I imported configuration file (rcfile-2.0) of some other machine (Ubuntu x86_64) with functional config and copied this to /home/<User>/.bluefish/rcfile-2.0 No results.

Hi. Paul Howarth and plus in charge, I did not specified DE because albeit I use Plasma, issue seems to reproduce at application level. I did not understand post to Gnome, when I experienced this in Plasma [5].
Created attachment 1213683 Image shows configuration from BlueFish 2.2.9 (KDE Plasma 5, Ptg_Br)

Hi,
bugzilla.gnome.org is the upstream bug tracker for bluefish; there was no implication that you are/were using Gnome.
I believe this is fixed in bluefish-2.2.10-1.fc24; can you check?
Yes, Paul Howarth. This is fixed. I can confirm against ..2-10 under F25. Thanks.
